social_posts.post_text: Since eight years of coming to the United States, it has been my dream to give back to my parents and that time has finally arrived. I was blessed to take my parents all over the country here from NYC to LA, trying exciting and different kinds of food here with them as well as my mother’s own supreme cooking! Our trip here has come to a close and I feel a little low now that I bid them bon voyage, but I will see you soon back home in Hyderabad! Thank you for your blessings and safe travels!! 🙏✈️❤️💯
📍Keywest Florida 🇺🇸 , Home of the sunset!! 🌅🏝️

This was my very first picture when I came to the United States, in Miami to be exact. Whenever I visit Miami, I always go back to this spot and get nothing but good vibes every time. That was eight years ago, when I came here without knowing anybody besides myself. Just off-camera is where I leased my first apartment as well, at the Sail on Brickell. This quickly became my favorite spot in the United States to sit and daydream about the future and hang out with the friends I made along the way…eight years later, I am very lucky and blessed to take the same photo with my parents in the same exact spot. 🇺🇸
